{"lemma":"وَحْدَةٍ","slug":"وَحْدَةٍ","root":"#.ح.د","root_slug":"_-ح-د","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ح-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n41730","n41737"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%88%D9%8E%D8%AD%D9%92%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"unit (a standard measure of a quantity)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"unit (a group within an organization that has been assigned a specific duty or function)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"unit; module (part of a book or educational course)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"union, unity; oneness (the state of being united as one)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"loneliness, solitude (a feeling of depression resulting from being alone)","examples":[{"text":"الْوَحْدَةُ قَدْ تَكُونُ فُرْصَةً لِلتَّفْكِيرِ وَٱسْتِكْشَافِ الذَّاتِ.","english":"Solitude can be an opportunity for reflection and self-discovery."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/waħ.da/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n41730","headword_ar":"وحّدهُ","root":"wHd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tawoHiydN","text_ar":"تَوْحِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made it one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called it one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) like as one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vanaAhu","text_ar":"ثَنَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"val~avahu","text_ar":"ثَلَّثَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, L:) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aH~adahu","text_ar":"اَحَّدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Similar verbs are formed from the other nouns significant of numbers, to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$arapN","text_ar":"عَشَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Esh-Sheybánee, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wH~d liA@moraA^atihi","text_ar":"وحّد لِا@مْرَاَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinodahaA","text_ar":"عِنْدَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He remained one night with his wife:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner the verb is used in relation to any saying or action. (TA, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sab~aEa","text_ar":"سَبَّعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wH~d A@ll~`ha","text_ar":"وحّد ا@للّٰهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tawoHiydN","text_ar":"تَوْحِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He asserted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"declared, God to be one: he asserted, declared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"preferred belief in, the unity of God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AH~dhu","text_ar":"احّدهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, L.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~awoHiydu","text_ar":"التَّوْحِيدُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The belief in God alone;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his unity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)"}],"source_refs":["K","S","L"]},{"entry_id":"n41737","headword_ar":"وَحْدَةٌ","root":"wHd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state of being alone,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apart from others; solitariness; solitude."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sb, S.) See 1. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHodapu Alqabori","text_ar":"وَحْدَةُ القَبْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The solitude of the grave"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b3-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapu AlwaHodapi","text_ar":"لَيْلَةُ الوَحْدَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The night of solitude;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the first night after burial: so called because the soul is believed to remain in the grave during this night, and then to depart to the place appointed for the residence of good souls until the last day, or to the appointed prison in which wicked souls await their final doom. See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapN AlwaHo$api","text_ar":"لَيْلَةٌ الوَحْشَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}